ad_creative_bodies:
We have the solutions and resources to tackle the climate crisis and inequality side by side. But so far, governments have failed to do what is necessary.

This election is an opportunity to win a Just Transition that ensures no one is left behind as we move away from fossil fuels.

So what does a Just Transition mean?
✅ Investing in decarbonizing our economy from bottom to top—at a minimum of 2% of GDP per year, comparable to World War II levels of investment.
✅ Empowering and resourcing Indigenous and local communities to lead their transitions and have actual decision-making power.
✅ Funding training and low-carbon job creation to prepare workers for the growing sustainable economy
✅ Putting a halt to fossil fuel subsidies that are driving the crisis, and making big polluters pay.
✅ Providing a permanent, guaranteed livable basic income to support families and communities, and ensure income security through the climate crisis and beyond, regardless of work status.

We have enough for everyone. Canada can tackle the climate crisis and inequality side by side, but needs courageous leaders to make it happen.

This is why we are mobilizing to elect Courage to Lead champions on September 20th. Join us: https://act.leadnow.ca/make_calls/?source=fb

Are you ready to elect candidates with the courage to lead? Here is all you need to know about our election campaign. 

Canada has the resources to tackle the climate crisis and inequality side by side. But by and large, our politicians have shied away from doing what is necessary.

This election, we need to elect leaders ready to step up to deliver a Just Transition and a Basic Income that ensures a just and safe future for all.

But to win, we need YOU. Join our Victory Squad—a cohort of star volunteers who will help us make thousands of phone calls in key ridings 👉 https://act.leadnow.ca/join-the-victory-squad/?source=fb
